gh to its eastern terminus. At the eastern end, the aftershock zone\nbroadens and extends northwest towards the southern extension of the\nnorthwest-striking, right-lateral Petrified Springs fault system. The eastern\nsection hosts significantly fewer aftershocks than the western section, but has\nmore moment release.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Feb 2021 00:18:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Feb 2021 16:53:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-02"}
